{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "Vine",
  "description": "MESH_DEFORM_AND_CURVE_GEOMETRY_DESIGN P3 demo — node.tube_from_path growing along a climbing spiral. A circular path (node.range angle -> cos/sin via node.array_math -> node.combine_xy) plus a linear lift (node.range) builds a helical centerline — a vine wrapping a pole. node.tube_from_path sweeps a tube around it; `radius_scale` is a per-point growth-front ramp (node.range fraction -> node.array_math threshold against the grow_phase outer param) so the tube's radius collapses to 0 past the front instead of the whole vine popping in at once — sweeping grow_phase 0 to 1 visibly grows the vine from base to tip. node.make_triangles gives it topology + normals, then node.twist_mesh adds a slight secondary spiral along its own climb for texture. A beat ramp on grow_phase = the vine grows over bars on stage.",
  "presetMetadata": {
